##Annual reports of 229 a-share companies delayed, with a number of Hubei companies considering deferral

I-CAIJING

CAIJING magazine official Wechat. "CAIJING" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was first published in 1998, adhering to the news concept of "independence, exclusiveness and originality" , and is known for authoritative, impartial and professional reporting, it is a must-read publication for policy-makers, researchers and managers in the field of politics and economics.

The outbreak not only severely affected the resumption of work, a number of a-share companies also delayed the disclosure of annual reports. As the disaster area, Hubei Province listed companies disclosure of the impact of annual reports are gradually emerging

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
By Wayne Wang, CAIJING correspondent

Editor | Ling Lu

The sudden onset of COVID-19, not only seriously affected the resumption of business, a number of companies also delayed the annual report disclosure.

"Our company's annual report was originally scheduled for the end of March, but due to the epidemic, auditors are now required to be quarantined for 14 days. The company plans to delay the disclosure of the annual report and is now waiting for the group's approval, " a listed company secretary in Fujian Province told CAIJING, the timing of the disclosure depends on the auditor's entry time.

Unlike the company's annual report, which has not yet been revised, many listed companies'2019 annual report disclosure date has been delayed for the first time.

According to Ju Chao's statistics, as of February 24,2020, a total of 266 companies in Shanghai and Shenzhen had initially changed the disclosure time of their 2019 annual reports, 229 of which were delayed.

Wind data shows that only 11 companies disclosed their annual reports for 2019 as of February 24,2020, a significant reduction from the 41 companies that disclosed their annual reports as of February 24,2019.

As the disaster area, Hubei Province listed companies disclosure of the impact of annual reports are gradually emerging.

CAIJING reporters interviewed a number of Hubei listed companies found that, due to the delay in resuming work, traffic blockade, isolation and other factors, auditors can not enter after the Spring Festival, some companies have not yet changed the disclosure date of annual reports, consider extending.

Although the CSRC has now made it clear that if it is difficult to disclose the 2019 annual report on the original appointment date, it may apply for an extension to disclose the annual report before April 30,2020. However, a number of partners and auditors interviewed said that the current corporate resumption rate is not high, due to offline audit work can not be carried out, may not be in time at the end of April, called for further extension.

For companies whose main businesses or audit teams are listed in Hubei, Li Chao, vice chairman of the CSRC, said that arrangements will be made after a comprehensive assessment of the impact of the epidemic, as well as effective alignment with existing laws, regulations and relevant rules.

The number of postponements has increased rapidly

The number of listed companies postponing the disclosure of their 2019 annual reports has increased rapidly recently due to the impact of the COVID-19 epidemic and the inability to conduct full on site audits, among other reasons. According to statistics from Juchao Information, the number of companies delaying the annual report on the Shanghai and Shenzhen Stock Markets Rose from 168 on February 19 to 229 on February 24, an increase of 36.31 percent.

"affected by the epidemic, the corporate sector, including finance, can not have more than 50 percent of people working every day, and the same will be true for the next week, " a 600990.Sh  source told CAIJING on Feb. 21, on the same day, 2 auditors came into the field. Due to the restriction of the number of workers returned by the company and the Audit Organization during the epidemic period, about 11 members of the audit team could not all be present. The follow-up should be connected with the financial personnel in batches.

The office address is located at Sichuang Electronics Co. , Ltd. in Hefei, Anhui Province. The first appointment date for the 2019 annual report is February 29, and the first change time is April 25.

Unlike some of Sichuang's auditors, some public company auditors are not yet in the game.

"We had done most of the annual report audits years ago, and some local audits were planned to be done after the Spring Festival. We did not expect the epidemic to be so serious. Now, even if the auditors could come, it would take another 14 days of isolation before they could work, " a person in the Securities Department of 600885.Sh  told CAIJING, the company communicated with the auditor, who was expected to return in early March.

HONGFA annual report, the first pre-disclosure time for April 2, the first change time for April 30.

Listed companies to disclose the annual report behind a wide range of delays, is under the epidemic, around the requirements for the resumption of work, isolation, and other factors, disrupting the audit organization's work rhythm.

"At present, the team has resumed work, temporarily taking a remote audit, requesting enterprises to provide electronic versions of the report data for analysis, and making project drafts at home, " An audit manager of the Big Four told Caijing, but inventory count, management interviews, field visits and other on-site work can not be carried out, "a so few people, to audit dozens of hundreds of companies, to tell the truth is very nervous, not to mention this year. "

However, some bank staff and upstream and downstream companies have not returned to work normally. The confirmation letters sent by the firm to them on bank deposits, receivables and payables, etc. , have not been received, greatly affecting the speed of the reply letters, the work progress of the above-mentioned audit manager has also been slowed down.

A fujian-based auditor said local projects were beginning to arrive, but travel projects were even more difficult: "Many local hotels are closed, so even when audited companies go to work, there is no place to stay. "

"It is very difficult for a listed company with a large number of subsidiaries and a complex business to ensure the quality of the audit in a short period of time, " said a partner at a large domestic Accounting networks and associations, but not one of the procedures should be omitted, because if the listed company explosion, "the final accounts will be blamed on the auditor. ".

Regions with more publicly traded companies also had the highest number of companies reporting delays in 2019.

According to statistics from Caijing, as of February 24,40 listed companies in Guangdong Province were temporarily ranked first in the regional distribution of the delayed listed companies disclosed in the 2019 annual report, followed by Beijing and Zhejiang.

In the manufacturing industry, including chemical, automobile and light industry, a total of about 148 listed companies delayed disclosure of annual reports, accounting for 64.63% .

In the view of a person from a listed company, in the audit work, some work needs to be carried out on the spot, such as inventory taking and other work. Because of the epidemic situation, the auditors can not enter the market, and the corresponding work can not be carried out on time, this is especially true for manufacturing companies with large inventories.

The influence of Hubei Company is beginning to show

As the disaster area, Hubei Listed Company Annual Report Audit problems are gradually emerging.

As of February 19, there are three companies with offices in Hubei Province, namely CITIC Special Steel (Url) , Tianmao group (Url) and 600136.Sh  .

As of February 24, the number of companies postponing the annual report in Hubei Province has increased to five, with the addition of five-party photoelectricity (Url) and St Double Ring (000707.SZ ) .

CAIJING reporter found that a number of Hubei enterprises that have not yet delayed the disclosure of their 2019 annual report are considering deferral.

On February 20, the COVID-19 of Hubei Province issued a notice saying that enterprises involved in the prevention and control of the epidemic, public utilities, the necessities of life of the people and other related enterprises involved in the important national economy and people's livelihood are excluded, all types of enterprises shall resume work no earlier than March 10 at 24:00.

Even if the Hubei enterprises have resumed work, on-site audit work can not be carried out.

000759.Sz  , a leading supermarket in Hubei Province, has a resumption rate of more than 80% and its annual report will be released on March 27. A person from its securities department told a reporter from Caijing, "The audit group in the annual report has conducted an audit before the end of the year. Due to the impact of traffic blockades and isolation, some on-site stocktaking has been delayed. Through communication with the CSRC, we are seeking disclosure before the end of April. "

The same problem applies to the annual report audit of the Josiah Goddard infrared (Url) , Angel Yeast (600298.Sh ) office in Hubei Province.

The 20-day notice has caused the on-site audit of Hubei listed companies that have not resumed work to be postponed again.

"A further 20-day extension will no doubt constrain the entry audit. The company is communicating with the firm to assess the impact and has no clear opinion on the timing of the disclosure, " 000988.Sz  told reporters.

Huagong Technology Audit Project leader bluntly: "The audit of the Central Wuhan Branch of the employees are mostly Hubei locals, can only stay at home. ". Based on past audit experience, pre-trial usually takes place in november-december and formal annual reviews begin in January, at least two months and usually in March."

A listed company person to "Caijing" reporter analysis, as a disaster area, affected by the epidemic factors, Hubei listed companies more affected by the audit of annual reports, is expected to delay disclosure of the number of companies will gradually increase.

According to Wind, 107 listed companies in Hubei Province are required to disclose their annual reports for 2019.

Although the CSRC has now made it clear that if it is difficult to disclose the 2019 annual report on the original appointment date, it may apply for an extension to disclose the annual report before April 30,2020. But a number of partners and auditors who responded to the report called for a further delay.

Recently, the Association issued a special reminder to the Accounting networks and associations, said it is in close communication with the relevant departments, and wrote to the relevant departments, requested to study the issue of the annual report disclosure delay.

A number of Hubei listed companies told Caijing that the Hubei Securities Regulatory Bureau and the Stock Exchange are aware that the disclosure of their annual reports has been affected by the epidemic, and there is no specific plan for how to deal with the failure to disclose the annual reports by the end of April.

"The quality of the audit will definitely be affected if the auditors do not go to the site. The on-site work is a hard and fast rule for annual report audit, and the absence of this part is also against the rules,"Ge Changyin, an associate professor of accounting at the School of Economics and management at China Agricultural University, told reporters.

However, in order to more accurately assess the impact of the epidemic on listed companies, the regulatory authorities are working closely to carry out risk screening, the various types of market subject affected by the extent of the epidemic to determine, to make response arrangements.

Such as the Shanghai Stock Exchange Organization to understand the impact of the epidemic on the production and operation of listed companies, faced with pressure to resume work, put forward relevant solutions. At the same time, arrange the annual report to disclose the change of appointment date.

"What the epidemic has taught me is that the more informatized the firms are, the more effective the off-site audits will be, " said a partner of a large domestic Accounting networks and associations, adding that investment in audit software will be increased in the future, improve audit efficiency.

In the view of the market, the large-scale delay in the disclosure of the 2019 annual report of listed companies, in most cases, has little effect on investors'judgment of the General Direction of the value of the company, but will give the research company a little trouble on the details. Because the non-standard opinions that affect the value of the company's investments will be delayed accordingly, the timing of the change in the strategy of shareholders holding such stocks will be affected.

"However, the probability of non-standard audit opinions appearing in white horse stocks is relatively small, and may appear in small market-value companies, " Hou Dawei, deputy general manager of Cacao medical capital, told CAIJING.
